validateTree - A utility method that checks that the balancing and ordering invariants of the tree are satisfied.

### isMutable() {#a3285b051577e1b91acd2aaa51d1a99d1}

<MemberDefinition
  template={<>template &lt;typename ImutInfo&gt;</>}
  prototype={<>bool llvm::ImutAVLTree&lt; ImutInfo &gt;::isMutable () const</>}
  labels = {["inline"]}>
isMutable - Returns true if the left and right subtree references (as well as height) can be changed.

If this method returns false, the tree is truly immutable. Trees returned from an <a href="/docs/api/classes/llvm/imutavlfactory">ImutAVLFactory</a> object should always have this method return true. Further, if this method returns false for an instance of <a href="/docs/api/classes/llvm/imutavltree">ImutAVLTree</a>, all subtrees will also have this method return false. The converse is not true.

Definition at line <a href="/docs/api/files/include/include/llvm/include/llvm/adt/immutableset-h/#l00246">246</a> of file <a href="/docs/api/files/include/include/llvm/include/llvm/adt/immutableset-h">ImmutableSet.h</a>.
